1.Write Java code to determine the smallest number of three numbers entered by the user. 

code:
    import java.util.*;
    public class smallest {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
       int n1, n2, n3;
    Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
       n1 = input.nextInt();
       n2 = input.nextInt();
       n3 = input.nextInt();
        if(n1<=n2 && n1<=n3) {
           System.out.println("The smallest number entered is "+n1);
       }
        else if((n2<=n1) && (n2<=n3)) {
           System.out.println("The smallest number entered is "+n2);
        }
        else{
           System.out.println("The smallest number entered is "+n3);
       }
     }

2.Write Java code using Switch case.

code:
     import java.util.*;
     public class switch {

   public static void main(String[] args) {

       int n;
       Scanner input= new Scanner(System.in);
       n=input.nextInt();
       switch (n){
           case 1:
               System.out.println("Hufflepuff");
               break;
           case 2:
               System.out.println("Gryffindor");
               break;
           case 3:
               System.out.println("Slytherin");
               break;
           case 4:
               System.out.println("Ravenclaw");
               break;
           default:
               System.out.println("Enter a number from 1 to 4");
       }
   }
}

3. Which of the following loops will execute the body of loop even when condition controlling the loop is initially false?
a) do-while*
b) while
c) for
d) none of the above

4.Write a program that prints all the odd numbers from 25 to 1 (in decreasing order)using while loop.

code:
 public class oddnumber {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int number = 25;
        
        while (number >= 1) {
            if (number % 2 != 0) {
                System.out.print(number +" " );
            }
            number--; 
        }
    }
}

5.Write a program that prints the sum of first n numbers, n is the input from the user.

code:
   import java.util.Scanner;
   public class Sum {
  public static void main(String arg[]) {
    Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
    //Enter the number upto which you wish to find the sum, in the input console
    int number = scan.nextInt();
    int sum = 0;
       for (int i=0;i<=number;i++ ) {
      // Write your logic here
      sum+=i;
    }
    System.out.print(sum);
    }
}

6.write a java code using do while loop to print first n integers starting from 0 in reverse order.

code: import java.util.*;
public class dowhile {

   public static void main(String[] args) {
     int n;
     Scanner input= new Scanner(System.in);
     n=input.nextInt();
     int counter=n;
     do{
         System.out.println(counter);
         counter--;
     }while(counter>=0);
   }
   }

7.Which loop construct in Java is best suited when the number of iterations is known? 
ans:(a)
    a) for loop*
    b) while loop
    c) do-while loop
    d) break statement 

8.What is the purpose of the continue statement in a loop? 
ans:(b)
   a) To exit the loop immediately
   b) To skip the current iteration and move to the next iteration *
   c) To terminate the program
   d) To execute a specific block of code 

9.What is an infinite loop? 
ans:(b)
  a) A loop that executes only once
  b) A loop that never terminates naturally*
  c) A loop that contains an unreachable code block
  d) A loop that uses the continue statement 

10. Which statement is used to exit a loop prematurely? 
ans:(c)
  a) return statement
  b) continue statement
  c) break statement*
  d) exit statement 
